text: <@U0MRVA8R4>: I agree with your opinion about the rails and trains. After all, we are too technical for now IMO. We need set the standard and benchmark of API, architecture, performance, security, audit, monitoring and etc before we write the code. Of cause the obc and sawtooth are good reference, but we really need a common agreement regarding what is a real industry level blockchain and what kinds of KPI we need.
This is meant to be the task performed by the Arch WG and Identity WG
Although this can be an iterative process. For example bit coin was born from a short introduction and a reference implementation the properties emerged as the system grew.
